main event: A small white star-like object was observed in Mosinee, Wisconsin, on April 22, 1964.
interesting points: The object was visible for about five minutes, The observation was reported to have been made from Hwy 34 near the Marathon & Portage County line, Witnesses described the object as rapidly moving in a straight line from North to South, The sighting was reported five days after it occurred, The object was evaluated as probably being a satellite or shooting star.
witness description: Students aged 14 to 20 years from Wisconsin
